body:
 - move last_updated in Freshness to timestamp
 - Freshness_status in Node_info section will looks like:
{
0: {'Last_updated_time': '2019-01-22 13:27:44+00:00', 'Has_write_consensus': True}, 
1: {'Last_updated_time': '2019-01-22 13:27:44+00:00', 'Has_write_consensus': True}, 
2: {'Last_updated_time': '2019-01-22 13:27:44+00:00', 'Has_write_consensus': True}}
}

- do not process any View Change related messages (including ViewChangeDone from Current State for primary propagation) until the current catchup is finished;
- this fixes initialization of a node where we mixed together initial catchup and primary propagation (initial view change);
- also fixed recovering when primary is disconnected and (n-f)th node joins the pool

Signed-off-by: ashcherbakov <alexander.sherbakov@dsr-company.com>

- do not process any View Change related messages (including ViewChangeDone from Current State for primary propagation) until the current catchup is finished;
- this fixes initialization of a node where we mixed together initial catchup and primary propagation (initial view change);
- also fixed recovering when primary is disconnected and (n-f)th node joins the pool

- increment indy-crypto to the latest stable;
- improve bls crypto tests;
- get rid of tmp fixes for length in crypto
- added more tests

- building of python-indy-crypto deb is moved to indy-crypto repo;
- increment indy-crypto version
- indy-crypto is renamed (python3 prefix is removed)

- Supported indy-crypto for working with BLS signatures;
- Created separate classed (with unit and integration tests) for BLS-related logic;
- Supported BLS sigs in consensus protocol;

- Fixed the problem with catch-up of disconnected nodes;
- Fixed demotion (suspension) of nodes
- Fixed the problem with catch-up of demoted nodes

- use encoded (integer) values as txn type
- rename txn.py to constants.py (resolve TODOs);
- support NYM and NODE commands in CLI by both name and value.
